// MARK: - Menu bar render dedup
// Setting `button.image = ...` with a non-template NSImage causes AppKit
// to recompose the status item replicant view, which in turn flips
// `button.effectiveAppearance` — re-firing the KVO that triggered the
// render. That feedback loop pegged the main thread (~600 renders/s) and
// was the dominant CPU consumer. The two dedup keys below break the loop:
// `lastRenderedKey` skips re-assigning an identical image, and
// `lastResolvedIsDark` filters spurious appearance KVO fires.
